## 'data.frame':    203741 obs. of  9 variables:
##  $ vararg     : logi  TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE ...
##  $ metaprogram: logi  FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE ...
##  $ missing    : logi  FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE ...
##  $ unevaluated: logi  FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE ...
##  $ effects    : logi  FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE ...
##  $ reflection : logi  FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE ...
##  $ pack_name  : chr  "abind" "abind" "abind" "abind" ...
##  $ fun_name   : chr  "`abind`" "`acorn`" "`acorn.default`" "`adrop`" ...
##  $ formal_pos : int  0 4 4 4 4 1 1 4 4 13 ...
join_positions <- function(formal_pos, lazy) {
    pos <- 1 + sort(formal_pos[!lazy])
    paste("<", paste(pos, collapse = ","), ">;", sep="")
}

signatures <-
    signature_table %>%
    mutate(lazy = vararg | metaprogram | missing | unevaluated | effects | reflection) %>%
    group_by(pack_name, fun_name, formal_pos) %>%
    summarize(lazy = any(lazy)) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    group_by(pack_name, fun_name) %>%
    summarize(strict_args = join_positions(formal_pos, lazy)) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    mutate(signature = paste("strict", fun_name, strict_args, sep = " ")) %>%
    group_by(pack_name) %>%
    summarize(content = paste(signature, collapse = "\n")) %>%
    ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'pack_name', 'fun_name'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'pack_name'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
datatable(signatures)
## Warning in instance$preRenderHook(instance): It seems your data is too big
## for client-side DataTables. You may consider server-side processing: https://

save_signatures <- function(pack_name, content) {
    filepath <- path_join(c(params$sigdir, pack_name))
    write_file(content, filepath)
}

dir_create(params$sigdir)
pwalk(signatures, save_signatures)
